<body>
    <h1>Defining Responses</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"DefiningResponses-SupportedSuccessResponseCodes"><strong>=
Supported Success Response Codes</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">HTTP Status Code</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Status</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">200</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">OK</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The standard response for successful HTTP reques=
ts, should contain a request body</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">201</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Created</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The request has been fulfilled, resulting in the=
 creation of a new resource</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">202</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Accepted</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The request has been accepted for processing, bu=
t the processing has not been completed. The request might or might not be =
eventually acted upon, and may be disallowed when processing occurs</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">204</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">No Content</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The server successfully processed the request an=
d is not returning any content</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"DefiningResponses-SupportedFailureResponseCodes"><strong>Supporte=
d Failure Response Codes</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">HTTP Status Code</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Status</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">400</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Bad Request</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The server <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker"=
 data-ref=3D"6b912db6-bee4-4878-b072-10f0f5dedaa0">cannot or will not proc<=
/span>ess the request due to an apparent client error</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">404</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Not Found</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The requested resource could not be found but ma=
y be available in the future, subsequent requests by the client are permiss=
ible</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">409</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Conflict</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The request could not be completed due to a conf=
lict with the current state of the target resource. Can be used when optimi=
stic locking is in use.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">500</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: center;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Internal Server Er=
ror</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">A generic error message, given when an unexpecte=
d condition on the server was encountered and no more specific HTTP respons=
e code is suitable</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
    </div>
